Privacy Policy for Vocabulens

Last updated: November 1, 2025

At Vocabulens, we respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our mobile application.

1. Information We Collect

We aim to keep data collection minimal. Depending on how you use the App, we may collect:

Usage Data: Information about how you interact with the App, such as features used, time spent, and performance data.

Device Information: Basic device data like model, operating system version, and app version, used to improve stability and compatibility.

Crash & Diagnostic Data: Anonymous reports that help us fix bugs and improve performance.

Analytics Data: Aggregated statistics (e.g., number of users, language preferences) to understand app usage and enhance user experience.

We do not collect personal information such as name, email, or contact details unless you explicitly provide them through optional features (e.g., feedback form or login system).

2. How We Use Information

We use collected data only to:

Improve app performance and user experience

Monitor and analyze app usage

Detect, prevent, and fix technical issues

Support future development and updates

3. Data Sharing and Disclosure

We do not sell or rent your data.
We may share limited information with trusted third-party services (such as analytics or crash reporting providers) solely for app improvement purposes. These services are required to protect your data and comply with privacy regulations.

4. Data Retention

We retain anonymous analytics and diagnostic data only as long as needed for analysis and performance improvement. If you delete the app, no further data is collected.

5. Your Rights

Depending on your location, you may have the right to:

Request deletion of your data

Opt out of analytics tracking (usually via your device settings)

You can also contact us through the app’s feedback option if you have any privacy-related questions.

6. Children’s Privacy

Vocabulens does not knowingly collect data from children under 13 (or under the minimum age in your country). If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us so we can remove it.

7. Security

We use reasonable measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.

8. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted within the App and/or on the app store listing. Continued use of the App after changes means you accept the updated policy.

9. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through the Help or Feedback section within the app.
